<br>
Grouping was rewarded, since if you wanted the very best xp you had to go deep in a dungeon such as juggernauts in sebilis, mines in chardok, castle in velk, cazic thule, rats in dragon necropolis etc... The mobs there were numerous and social, hard hitting and most summoned, making grouping pretty much mandatory. At the same time, &quot;imperfect&quot; groups and soloers could still operate effectively against low blue mobs.<br>
<br>
PoP totally changed that by destroying the solo ability of any class that can't solo without taking hits... but with mobs with low MR, giving insane xp, rootable, snarable, non summoning, it totally changed the grouping vs soloing balance that existed right before PoP, i.e. there's no point in grouping except for fun if you can solo, and if you can't, then you have to allocate at least 30 min and usually a lot more to get anything started.  <br>
<br>
In order for balance to be restored, first, minimal soloing ability must be restored for every class. I don't mean that every class should solo the same - not at all - but that everyone should be able to get &quot;reasonable&quot; solo xp in a gaming session. <br>
<br>
As far as grouping goes, there has to be a point for grouping. I don't know how to do this since basically 95% of what a group can kill in PoP can be easily soloed as well. One idea might be to revamp some zones and make them a lot tougher on the soloers by removing outdoor flags, make all mobs summon, make all mobs immune to harmony and lull, increase aggro range, and then double or triple the xp return.<br>
